ected officials but rather in initiatives at the subparliamentary level. Case studies on a range of topics, from breastfeeding and sustainable pest management promotion to programs such as Canada's Action Plan on Food Security, tell a story of misguided campaigns and missed opportunities. Real change, this inspiring volume suggests, is possible. It will come when advocacy groups develop innovative strategies of influencing decision makers more resistant to public pressure: business lobbies well connected to government agencies, middle managers, and ministries unused to collaborating across departmental mandates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgriculture and statezCanadavCase studies. 0aAgriculture durablexCas, Études dezCanada. 0aAgriculturexCase studiesxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aAgriculturezCanadaxCas, Études dexAspect social. 0aAlimentsxCas, Études dexSécuritéxMesureszCanada. 0aCivil societyzCanadavCase studies. 0aEnvironmental protectionzCanadavCase studies. 0aEnvironnementxCas, Études dexProtectionzCanada. 0aFood securityzCanadavCase studies. 0aFoodxQualityxCanada. 0aFoodzCanadaxCase studiesxSafety measures. 0aGroupes de pressionxCas, Études dezCanada. 0aPolitique agricolexCas, Études dezCanada. 0aPressure groupszCanadavCase studies. 0aSécurité alimentairexCas, Études dezCanada. 0aSociété civilexCas, Études dezCanada. 0aSustainabilityxCanadaxElectronic books. 0aSustainable agriculturezCanadavCase studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh1 aAbergel, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbergel, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBas, Japji Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1